The paper deals with modelling diffusion processes on dynamic contact networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with modelling diffusion on dynamic contact networks, which is a subfield of social and information networks. 
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is also likely as the paper deals with modelling diffusion in social networks. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper introduces a new diffusion model and a new graph model to generate synthetic traces. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper investigates how diffusion can be controlled and develops new methods to hinder diffusion, which can be related to optimization and control problems. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is a possible category as the paper mentions cybersecurity as one of the areas where modelling diffusion on dynamic contact networks is important.
